                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/664.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">([<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1912-06-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                            notBefore="1912-06-02T00:00:00-05:29">undated</date>;] <hi rend="italic"
                            >Received June 3, 1912—12.51 a.m.</hi>)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Consul at Santiago telegraphs:</p>
                <p>La Maya, town of 4,000, completely destroyed by insurgents last night by fire.
                    Defended by seven rurales.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
